@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{gptel-extras.el} extends @samp{gptel}, the Emacs package that integrates various Large Language Models---ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Perplexity, local models, and others---into Emacs buffers. While @samp{gptel} provides the core infrastructure for sending prompts and receiving responses, @samp{gptel-extras.el} adds workflows and conveniences that make day-to-day use more productive.

The package depends on @samp{gptel} (version 0.7.1 or later) and @samp{paths} (for directory path resolution).

The extensions fall into several thematic areas:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Aider-style context management.} Commands for generating a repository map (via the external @samp{aider} tool), caching it with configurable time-to-live and git-aware invalidation, and automatically injecting both the map and a project conventions file into the @samp{gptel} context before each request (@ref{Aider context management}).

@item
@strong{Conversation management.} Automatic saving of new @samp{gptel} buffers to a dedicated directory, continuation of conversations across linked buffers, and a workaround for unresponsive @samp{gptel} sessions (@ref{Conversation management}).

@item
@strong{ChatGPT import.} Bulk import of conversations exported from ChatGPT into Org files (@ref{ChatGPT import}).

@item
@strong{Commit summarization.} Sending selected commit diffs from a Magit log buffer to an LLM for changelog-style summaries (@ref{Commit summarization}).

@item
@strong{Search integration.} A command that simultaneously opens a web search and queries a configured AI model (e.g., Perplexity Sonar) with the same query (@ref{Search integration}).

@item
@strong{Email drafting.} Integration with @samp{mu4e} and @samp{org-msg} for LLM-assisted email reply drafting (@ref{Email drafting with mu4e}).

@item
@strong{Gptel tools.} A collection of tools---filesystem editing, bibliography search, and entry addition---that @samp{gptel} can invoke via its tool-use feature, plus a macro for defining tool presets (@ref{Tools}).

@item
@strong{Model-specific workarounds.} Automatic Mullvad VPN activation for Gemini requests and a command for fixing garbled characters in LLM output (@ref{Model-specific workarounds}).

@item
@strong{General convenience commands.} Toggling default major mode, navigating to the end of a buffer before sending, rewriting function definitions via Embark, and more (@ref{General convenience commands}).
@end itemize

