@node Commit summarization
@section Commit summarization

@findex gptel-extras-summarize-commit-diffs
When reviewing a series of commits in a @samp{magit-log-mode} buffer, you may want a quick, high-level summary of what changed. The command @code{gptel-extras-summarize-commit-diffs} takes the active region in the log buffer, extracts the diffs for all commits within that region, and sends them to the LLM with a prompt requesting an Org-mode-formatted changelog summary.

The summary is displayed in a dedicated @samp{*Commit Summary*} buffer. The prompt is structured using the template in @code{gptel-extras-changelog-file}, which helps the LLM produce output organized by package or feature.

With a prefix argument (@samp{C-u}), the command includes full diff content with unified context rather than the default three-line unified diff. This can help the LLM understand broader context around each change.

This command must be invoked from a @samp{magit-log-mode} buffer with an active region spanning the commits of interest.

@node Aider context management
@section Aider context management

These commands manage the repository map and conventions file that provide project-level context to the LLM@. The repository map is generated by the external @samp{aider} tool (@samp{aider --show-repo-map}) and cached in memory with configurable TTL and git-aware invalidation (@ref{Aider context options}).

@menu
* Showing and managing the repository map::
* Toggling automatic context injection::
@end menu

@node Showing and managing the repository map
@subsection Showing and managing the repository map

@findex gptel-extras-show-repo-map
The command @code{gptel-extras-show-repo-map} generates (or retrieves from cache) the repository map for the current project and displays it in a dedicated buffer named @samp{*Repo Map: PROJECT-NAME*}. Use this to inspect the map before deciding whether to include it in the context.

@findex gptel-extras-add-repo-map-to-context
The command @code{gptel-extras-add-repo-map-to-context} generates the repository map, removes any previously added map from the @samp{gptel} context, and then adds the current map with explanatory preamble text. The preamble instructs the LLM to use the map for understanding project structure and to request relevant files.

@findex gptel-extras-add-conventions-to-context
The command @code{gptel-extras-add-conventions-to-context} adds the @samp{conventions.md} file from the current project root to the @samp{gptel} context. The project root is determined by @code{gptel-extras-get-repo} (@ref{Functions}).

@findex gptel-extras-remove-repo-map-from-context
The command @code{gptel-extras-remove-repo-map-from-context} removes the repository map buffer from the @samp{gptel} context without deleting the buffer itself.

@findex gptel-extras-invalidate-repo-map-cache
The command @code{gptel-extras-invalidate-repo-map-cache} removes the cached repository map for the current project, forcing regeneration on the next request. This is useful after large structural changes that the git-aware invalidation might not capture (e.g., adding many new files without committing).

@node Toggling automatic context injection
@subsection Toggling automatic context injection

@findex gptel-extras-toggle-aider-files
The command @code{gptel-extras-toggle-aider-files} toggles both @code{gptel-extras-add-repo-map-to-context} and @code{gptel-extras-add-conventions-to-context} simultaneously. If both are currently disabled, they are enabled, and vice versa. This provides a quick way to switch between coding mode (with full project context) and general conversation mode (without it).

