@node Automatic context injection
@section Automatic context injection

@findex gptel-extras-add-context-files
The function @code{gptel-extras-add-context-files} is added as @samp{:before} advice on @code{gptel-send}. Before every request, it checks the user options @code{gptel-extras-add-repo-map-to-context} and @code{gptel-extras-add-conventions-to-context} (@ref{Aider context options}) and, when enabled, calls the corresponding commands to inject context.

@node Post-response hooks
@section Post-response hooks

@findex gptel-extras-alert-when-finished
The function @code{gptel-extras-alert-when-finished} is added to @code{gptel-post-response-functions}. After @samp{gptel} inserts a response, it checks @code{gptel-extras-alert-when-finished} (@ref{Alert options}) and, if the condition is met, displays an alert via the @samp{alert} package.

@findex gptel-extras-generate-latex-previews
The function @code{gptel-extras-generate-latex-previews} is intended for @code{gptel-post-response-functions}. When the current buffer is in Org mode and its @code{default-directory} matches @code{gptel-extras-dir}, the function generates @LaTeX{} previews by calling @code{org-latex-preview}. This provides automatic rendering of mathematical notation in @samp{gptel} conversation files.

@node Model-specific workarounds
@section Model-specific workarounds

@findex gptel-extras-set-mullvad
The function @code{gptel-extras-set-mullvad} is added as @samp{:around} advice on @code{gptel-curl-get-response}. When @code{gptel-model} is @code{gemini-pro}, it activates a Mullvad VPN connection (via @code{mullvad-connect-to-website}) before the request is sent, with an automatic disconnect timer set to @code{gptel-extras-gemini-mullvad-disconnect-after} minutes (@ref{Gemini and VPN options}). This bypasses location restrictions that Gemini imposes in certain regions.

The VPN connection is made silently (no user prompt). The @samp{mullvad} package must be installed and configured separately.

@node Running queries programmatically
@section Running queries programmatically

@findex gptel-extras-run-query
The function @code{gptel-extras-run-query} creates a new @samp{gptel} buffer from a query string, optionally setting a specific backend and model. It is used internally by @code{gptel-extras-search-and-ask-model} (@ref{Search integration}) and can be called from Lisp for any programmatic query dispatch.

The buffer name is a slugified version of the query with the appropriate file extension. If @samp{BACKEND} or @samp{MODEL} are nil, the global defaults are used.

@node Repository identification
@section Repository identification

@findex gptel-extras-get-repo
The function @code{gptel-extras-get-repo} determines the repository path for the current request. In Org mode, it checks the @samp{GPTEL_REPO} property at the document level; if not set, it prompts the user and stores the selection. In other modes, it uses @code{project-root} if a project is detected, falling back to a directory prompt.

@findex gptel-extras-get-repo-map
The function @code{gptel-extras-get-repo-map} returns the repository map for the current project, using the cached version if it is still valid (checked via @code{gptel-extras-repo-map-cache-valid-p}). When the cache is stale or empty, it calls @samp{aider --show-repo-map} to generate a fresh map and stores it along with the current timestamp and git HEAD reference.

@node Preset macro
@section Preset macro

@findex gptel-extras-make-tool-presets
The macro @code{gptel-extras-make-tool-presets} creates two @samp{gptel} presets for a given set of tools: a base preset that sets the active tools to exactly the specified list, and an additive preset (with @samp{+} appended to the name) that appends the tools to whatever tools are already active. This is useful for defining reusable tool configurations.

For example:

@lisp
(gptel-extras-make-tool-presets tools-web-search
  "web search tools"
  '(web_search browse_url))
@end lisp

This creates presets named @samp{tools-web-search} (sets tools to the two specified) and @samp{tools-web-search+} (adds them to existing tools).

@node Tools
@chapter Tools

@samp{gptel-extras.el} registers several tools that @samp{gptel} can invoke via its tool-use feature. These tools allow the LLM to interact with the filesystem and bibliography.

@menu
* Filesystem tools::
* Bib@TeX{} tools::
* Robustifying tool presets::
@end menu

@node Filesystem tools
@section Filesystem tools

Three filesystem tools are provided, forming a fallback chain for file modification:

@findex gptel-extras-edit-file
@enumerate
@item
@strong{edit@math{_file}} (@code{gptel-extras-edit-file}): The primary file editing tool. It applies a list of edits to a file, where each edit specifies an @code{:old_string} to find and a @code{:new_string} to replace it with. The tool first attempts an exact match; if that fails, it uses fuzzy matching with normalized whitespace, case-insensitive search, and flexible regex strategies.

@item
@strong{apply@math{_diff}}: Applies a unified diff (patch) to a file using the external @samp{patch} command. Useful when the LLM generates changes in diff format. Supports configurable patch options (@samp{-p0}, @samp{-p1}, etc.).

@item
@strong{replace@math{_file}@math{_contents}}: Replaces the entire content of a file. This is the last resort, as it requires sending the full file content and is therefore token-inefficient.
@end enumerate

All three tools modify files directly on disk without user confirmation.

@node Bib@TeX{} tools
@section Bib@TeX{} tools

@findex gptel-extras-citar-search
The tool @strong{search@math{_bibliography}} (@code{gptel-extras-citar-search}) searches the user's bibliography via @samp{citar}. It splits the search string into space-separated terms and returns entries matching all terms as whole words. The search is case-insensitive and supports pagination via @samp{limit} and @samp{offset} parameters.

Each result is a pair of @samp{(FORMATTED-CITATION . CITE-KEY)}. The default limit is 10 results; use -1 for no limit.

@findex gptel-extras-add-bib-entry
The tool @strong{add@math{_bib}@math{_entry}} (@code{gptel-extras-add-bib-entry}) adds a bibliographic entry for a URL, ISBN, or DOI to a specified Bib@TeX{} file. It delegates to @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} from @samp{zotra-extras.el} and returns the citation key of the newly added entry.

@node Robustifying tool presets
@section Robustifying tool presets

@findex gptel-extras--modify-value-append-fix
The function @code{gptel-extras--modify-value-append-fix} is added as @samp{:around} advice on @code{gptel--modify-value}. It normalizes @samp{:append} specifications in preset plists so that tool names (strings or symbols) are properly wrapped in a list when appending to an existing list value. Without this fix, appending tool names could be misinterpreted as string appends, causing errors.

